xamples":[{"text":"يَا كَرَوَانًا ضُكَّ فَأَكْبَأَنَّا\nفَشَنَّ بِٱلسَلْخِ فَلَمَّا شَنَّا … بَلَّ ٱلذُنَابَى عَبَسًا مُبِنَّا","english":"You thick-knee! Which when bumped will clew and toss dung and having hurled … moistens the tail with sticky soil!"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to don, to put on (دِرْع (dirʕ))","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"waterskin","tags":["collective"],"examples":[{"text":"\" إِنْ كَانَ عِنْدَكَ مَاءٌ بَاتَ فِي شَنٍّ فَٱسْقِنَا وَإِلَّا كَرَعْنَا \" . قَالَ عِنْدِي مَاءٌ بَاتَ فِي شَنٍّ . فَٱنْطَلَقَ وَٱنْطَلَقْنَا مَعَهُ إِلَى ٱلْعَرِيشِ فَحَلَبَ لَهُ شَاةً عَلَى مَاءٍ بَاتَ فِي شَنٍّ فَشَرِبَ ثُمَّ فَعَلَ مِثْلَ ذَٰلِكَ بِصَاحِبِهِ ٱلَّذِي مَعَهُ .","english":"‘If you have any water that has been kept overnight in a water skin, then give us some to drink, otherwise we will drink by putting out mouths in the basin.’ He said: ‘I have water that has been kept in a water skin. So he went and we went with him, to the shelter, where he milked a sheep for him and (mixed it with) the water that had been kept overnight in a water skin. He drank from it, then he did likewise for his Companion who was with him.”"}]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Middle Iranian borrowings related to Persian شنا (šanā, “swimming”)."},"ipa":["/ʃan.na/"]}